## Leveling

**No in-run level curve** (in-run character leveling removed in v0.3.7 — `NODES.gdd`
decisions log). HP is a flat **200**; permanent growth comes from the additive
HP/ATK/DEF pools (Rest excess, Sharpen), not a level ladder.

---

## Design Notes

* PumpKing is a two-phase character: build phase (pump up, stack shield, position)
  and release phase (fire head, detonate, repeat). The rhythm is pump → fire → detonate
  → survive → pump again.
* The head is both weapon and liability. While Rolling, PumpKing has no shield and
  reduced combat presence. Skilled play means timing the detonation for maximum AoE
  value while minimizing vulnerable time.
* Soul Form bridges the gap — it provides evasion during the vulnerable Rolling phase
  or lets PumpKing cross the arena to retrieve positioning after a head launch.
* The back-facing firing segment (120°–240°) enables retreating head launches without
  turning — fire behind you while running away, then detonate when enemies cluster.
* The 0.5 s pump inner CD means reaching 5 stacks takes at least 2.5 s of sustained
  pumping — a significant commitment during combat.

---

## Implementation Notes

### Godot Port Status (v0.5.3)
Ported to Godot as `Scripts/Protagonists/PumpKing/PumpKing.cs` + `Scenes/PumpKing.tscn`
(body + `NeckHead` child) and `Scripts/Protagonists/PumpKing/PumpKingHead.cs` +
`Scenes/PumpKingHead.tscn` (rolling head).
Sprites and body animations (idle/walk/jump/soul) are migrated. Notes/deviations vs.
the Unity source:
- **Shield** is implemented in the subclass via a new `CharacterController.AbsorbDamage`
  hook (default pass-through) — the Godot base has no shield/ammo machinery, unlike Unity.
- **Head physics** use a manual-kinematic `CharacterBody2D` + `MoveAndCollide` reflect
  (velocity is naturally pre-collision) plus a floor-rest/roll-friction pass so the
  still-timer can fire. Mouse steering (off by default in Unity) was not ported.
- **Soul entry resets pump stacks *and* shield** (GDD canon) — Unity cleared only the
  shield; resetting both keeps the shield == stacks×20 invariant.
- **Autonomous heads** (released on Soul entry) play the explode visual but deal no AoE.
- **No dead/stun body clip** exists in the delivered art — death freezes the frame with
  the base gray tint; stun uses the base `Anim.SpeedScale` freeze.
- **Follow-ups:** shield has no HUD binding yet; head 6-stage art is a single sheet sliced
  per stage + code scale (not distinct per-stage art); PumpKing is not yet a selectable
  protagonist (Pomegraknight remains the Arena/RunState default); animation frame timings
  want an in-editor polish pass on a real Godot build.

### Bug pass (v0.6.1)
Five issues found and fixed post-port; see the `KNOWLEDGE.md` "PumpKing head" caveat for
the full write-up:
- **Neck anchor was at waist height.** `NeckHead`/`FirePoint` sat at `(0, -19)`, ported
  directly from Unity's `headNeckOffset` (0.6 m) — but that offset doesn't transfer across
  sprite sheets with different proportions/pivots. Re-measured from the actual delivered
  art (collar top ≈ 28 px above origin, head graphic's own half-height ≈ 21.5 px) and moved
  to `(0, -48)` so the head sits on the collar instead of at the torso.
- **Launch velocity didn't include PumpKing's own movement**, and `PumpKingHead.MaxRollSpeed`
  unconditionally clamped horizontal speed every tick — including the very first tick right
  after `Init()`, before the head had moved at all — so the 12 m/s launch impulse was
  discarded immediately and the head never traveled on the throw. Fixed to (a) add
  PumpKing's `Velocity` to the launch vector and (b) only apply the roll-speed cap once the
  head has actually touched a floor (`_grounded`); bumped the launch impulse to 16 m/s.
- **Explosion radius/VFX audited, not a bug** — the 96 px / 3 m hit radius is real (not a
  sprite illusion); the VFX oversizes it by only ~9%. See the diagram from the debug session.
- **Shift nulled `_activeHead` immediately**, so `ExitSoul()` could never tell "released head
  still alive out there" from "no head," causing a phantom early reload (a fresh head could
  regrow on PumpKing's neck while the old autonomous one was still live) — contradicting this
  doc's own "PumpKing can still manually detonate after Soul ends." Fixed by keeping the
  reference through Soul (only nulling it once the head is confirmed exploded), which also
  required teaching `Explode()` to still deal AoE on a deliberate manual (BA) detonate even
  once a head is autonomous — previously that path was unreachable so this gap was hidden.
- **Knockback increased 9→15 m/s** — against a foe's 1200 px/s² deceleration, 9 m/s only
  pushed ~1.1 m (about one body length); 15 m/s pushes exactly 3 m, i.e. to the edge of the
  blast radius.

### State Machine
Three states (`PKState` enum: Normal, Rolling, Soul). State transitions are gated —
BA does nothing in Soul; Pump Up only works in Normal; firing head only works in
Normal with ammo available.

### Head Physics
`PumpKingHead` is a separate MonoBehaviour on the `rollingBallPrefab`. It handles:
- Rigidbody2D physics (gravity, bouncing, speed caps)
- Mouse steering (optional, off by default — pure physics)
- Bounce reflection using pre-collision velocity snapshot (`_prevVelocity`)
- Four explode conditions: still-timer, lifetime, manual (BA), contact with enemy
- Own Animator (`PK_Head_Projectile_AC`) with `HeadStage` (int 0–5) and `Explode` trigger

### Shield
Shield pool is managed via `currentShield`/`maxShield` from the base `CharacterController`.
`hasShield` bool is kept in sync. Shield clears on entering Rolling or Soul.

### Neck Head Visibility
The neck head child GameObject (`NeckHead`) has its own SpriteRenderer and Animator
(`PK_Head_Neck_AC`). It's hidden when the head is fired, shown again on reload
completion. The resolved explosion callback requests the shared reload.

### Ammo
The shared universal-ammo system has capacity **1**, reload amount **1**, and a **1.5 s**
reload delay. Every resolved head explosion triggers the reload; the neck head reappears
when the magazine is full.

